
A service = a background process running in your system
systemctl This is your control center for services

systemctl (control services) --
systemctl status nginx  -- is it running ?, process id, logs
sudo systemctl start nginx  -- start service(if stop)
sudo systemctl stop nginx  -- stop service
sudo systemctl restart nginx  -- restrart service (use after deployment, config chnage)
sudo systemctl enable nginx  -- enable service
sudo systemctl disable nginx  -- disable service

journalctl -- check Logs related
journalctl -u nginx  --  view logs of a service
journalctl -u nginx -f   -- follow logs live like tail
journalctl -u nginx --since "10 minutes ago"   -- show recent logs
journalctl -u nginx -p err  -- show only errors


/etc/systemd/system/ → Service files
This is where custom service configs live
